```

Computers think exactly the same way.

---

# Part 2 – Comparison Operators (15 min)

These are the symbols that allow Python to compare values.

| Operator | Meaning               | Example            |
| -------- | --------------------- | ------------------ |
| `>`      | Greater than          | `15 > 12`          |
| `<`      | Less than             | `10 < 12`          |
| `>=`     | Greater than or equal | `12 >= 12`         |
| `<=`     | Less than or equal    | `11 <= 12`         |
| `==`     | Equal to              | `age == 35`        |
| `!=`     | Not equal             | `gender != "Male"` |

Notice something important.

Equality is:

```python
==
```

NOT

```python
=
```

This is one of the biggest beginner mistakes.

